node.label: transportSession
node.content: This list contains the currently established Transport Sessions terminating at the given socket. Type : None

node.label: ipfixVersion
node.content: Used for Exporting Processes, this parameter contains the version number of the IPFIX protocol that the Exporter uses to export its data in this Transport Session. Used for Collecting Processes, this parameter contains the version number of the IPFIX protocol it receives for this Transport Session. If IPFIX Messages of different IPFIX protocol versions are transmitted or received in this Transport Session, this object contains the maximum version number. Type : uint16

node.label: protocol
node.content: The transport protocol used for receiving or transmitting IPFIX Messages. Protocol numbers are assigned by IANA. A current list of all assignments is available from <http://www.iana.org/>. Type : uint32

node.label: sourceAddress
node.content: The source address of the Exporter of the IPFIX Transport Session. This parameter is used with transport protocols like TCP(6) and UDP(17) that have the notion of addresses. SCTP(132) should use sctpAssocId instead. If SCTP(132) or any other protocol without the notion of addresses is used, this parameter is omitted. Type : inet:ip-address

node.label: destinationAddress
node.content: The destination address of the Collector of the IPFIX Transport Session. This parameter is used with transport protocols like TCP(6) and UDP(17) that have the notion of addresses. SCTP(132) should use sctpAssocId instead. If SCTP(132) or any other protocol without the notion of addresses is used, this parameter is omitted. Type : inet:ip-address

node.label: sourcePort
node.content: The transport protocol port number of the Exporter of the IPFIX Transport Session. If a transport protocol without the notion of ports is used, this parameter is omitted. Type : inet:port-number

node.label: destinationPort
node.content: The transport protocol port number of the Collector of the IPFIX Transport Session. If a transport protocol without the notion of ports is used, this parameter is omitted. Type : inet:port-number

node.label: sctpAssocId
node.content: The association id used for the SCTP session between the Exporter and the Collector of the IPFIX Transport Session. It is equal to the sctpAssocId entry in the sctpAssocTable defined in the SCTP-MIB. This parameter is only used if protocol has the value 132 (SCTP). In all other cases, the parameter is omitted. Type : uint32

node.content: Type : None

node.label: status
node.content: Status of the Transport Session. Type : transportSessionStatus

node.label: rate
node.content: The number of bytes per second transmitted by the Exporting Process or received by the Collecting Process. This parameter is updated every second. Type : yang:gauge32

node.label: packets
node.content: The number of packets transmitted by the Exporting Process or received by the Collecting Process. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of transportSessionDiscontinuityTime. Type : yang:counter64

node.label: bytes
node.content: The number of bytes transmitted by the Exporting Process or received by the Collecting Process. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of transportSessionDiscontinuityTime. Type : yang:counter64

node.label: messages
node.content: The number of messages transmitted by the Exporting Process or received by the Collecting Process. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of transportSessionDiscontinuityTime. Type : yang:counter64

node.label: discardedMessages
node.content: Used for Exporting Processes, this parameter indicates the number of messages that could not be sent due to internal buffer overflows, network congestion, routing issues, etc. Used for Collecting Process, this parameter indicates the number of received IPFIX Message that are malformed, cannot be decoded, are received in the wrong order or are missing according to the sequence number. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of transportSessionDiscontinuityTime. Type : yang:counter64

node.label: records
node.content: The number of Data Records transmitted by the Exporting Process or received by the Collecting Process. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of transportSessionDiscontinuityTime. Type : yang:counter64

node.label: templates
node.content: The number of Templates transmitted by the Exporting Process or received by the Collecting Process. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of transportSessionDiscontinuityTime. Type : yang:counter32

node.label: optionsTemplates
node.content: The number of Option Templates transmitted by the Exporting Process or received by the Collecting Process. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of transportSessionDiscontinuityTime. Type : yang:counter32

node.label: transportSessionStartTime
node.content: Timestamp of the start of the given Transport Session. This state parameter does not correspond to any object in the IPFIX MIB module. Type : yang:date-and-time

node.label: transportSessionDiscontinuityTime
node.content: Timestamp of the most recent occasion at which one or more of the Transport Session counters suffered a discontinuity. In contrast to ipfixTransportSessionDiscontinuityTime in the IPFIX MIB module, the time is absolute and not relative to sysUpTime. Type : yang:date-and-time

node.label: template
node.content: This list contains the Templates and Options Templates that are transmitted by the Exporting Process or received by the Collecting Process. Withdrawn or invalidated (Options) Template MUST be removed from this list. Type : None

node.label: observationDomainId
node.content: The ID of the Observation Domain for which this Template is defined. Type : uint32

node.label: templateId
node.content: This number indicates the Template Id in the IPFIX message. Type : uint16

node.label: setId
node.content: This number indicates the Set ID of the Template. Currently, there are two values defined. The value 2 is used for Sets containing Template definitions. The value 3 is used for Sets containing Options Template definitions. Type : uint16

node.label: accessTime
node.content: Used for Exporting Processes, this parameter contains the time when this (Options) Template was last sent to the Collector(s) or written to the file. Used for Collecting Processes, this parameter contains the time when this (Options) Template was last received from the Exporter or read from the file. Type : yang:date-and-time

node.label: templateDataRecords
node.content: The number of transmitted or received Data Records defined by this (Options) Template. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of templateDiscontinuityTime. Type : yang:counter64

node.label: templateDiscontinuityTime
node.content: Timestamp of the most recent occasion at which the counter templateDataRecords suffered a discontinuity. In contrast to ipfixTemplateDiscontinuityTime in the IPFIX MIB module, the time is absolute and not relative to sysUpTime. Type : yang:date-and-time

node.label: field
node.content: This list contains the (Options) Template fields of which the (Options) Template is defined. The order of the list corresponds to the order of the fields in the (Option) Template Record. Type : None

node.label: ieEnterpriseNumber
node.content: This parameter indicates the IANA enterprise number of the authority defining the Information Element Id. If the Information Element is not enterprise-specific, this state parameter is omitted. Type : uint32

Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of templateDiscontinuityTime. Type : yang:counter64

node.label: templateDiscontinuityTime
node.content: Timestamp of the most recent occasion at which the counter templateDataRecords suffered a discontinuity. In contrast to ipfixTemplateDiscontinuityTime in the IPFIX MIB module, the time is absolute and not relative to sysUpTime. Type : yang:date-and-time

node.label: field
node.content: This list contains the (Options) Template fields of which the (Options) Template is defined. The order of the list corresponds to the order of the fields in the (Option) Template Record. Type : None

node.label: ieId
node.content: This parameter indicates the Information Element Id of the field. Type : uint16

node.label: ieLength
node.content: This parameter indicates the length of the Information Element of the field. Type : uint16

node.label: ieEnterpriseNumber
node.content: This parameter indicates the IANA enterprise number of the authority defining the Information Element Id. If the Information Element is not enterprise-specific, this state parameter is omitted. Type : uint32

node.label: isFlowKey
node.content: If present, this is a Flow Key field. Type : empty

node.label: isScope
node.content: If present, this is a scope field. Type : empty

node.label: options
node.content: List of options reported by the Exporting Process. Type : None

node.label: name
node.content: Type : nameType

node.label: optionsType
node.content: Type : identityref

node.label: optionsTimeout
node.content: Time interval for periodic export of the options data. If set to zero, the export is triggered when the options data has changed. If not configured by the user, this parameter is set by the Monitoring Device. Type : uint32
